        "timestamp": "2018-04-01 14:58:10.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nIf I understand correctly, everything under org.openecomp.sdc.common.rest.api comes from a library that has been removed. If so, there must be a reason for it to be removed, and just copying that code here is not a good solution. I'd say either use the whatever library replaces the old one, or call Apache HTTP Client directly. The additional layer makes it more code to maintain (including testing, by the way), without much benefit. Have a look at sdc/common-app-api/src/main/java/org/openecomp/sdc/common/http. Can that be used instead?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
